				<td colspan="2"><span>What level are you?  Oh 60... hmm, I have only found one group where I couldn't meaningfully contribute in my entire EQ life.  I even posted about it here, I had a 60+ chanter and 60+ shaman in the group and was politely told not to bother with any songs they didn't have covered.  Other than that one occasion, I've never had any problem justifying my position in a group.  We do so many little things that make the group better that most groups never realize, that it's not even funny.  For example, we can slow a mob as it enters the camp taking away one CHeal needed from the cleric before the real slower dare's to cast. We can also OOS them so the slow lands easier.  That and I've never heard manasong played in downtime complained about.  Also, at 60 your DS should be nice and stacks with most others, making the MA very happy with you.  Oh yeah, and that 15% haste you talk about is the only thing that can blow out haste caps, so it's always liked.
